{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"2327a","heading":"Rehabilitation of Corps of Engineers constructed pump stations","label":"2327a Rehabilitation of Corps of Engineers constructed pump stations","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/ch36/schV","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextSection 160 of the Water Resources Development Act of 2020, referred to in subsec. (g), is , which is set out as a note under .section 160 of div. AA of Pub. L. 116–260section 2201 of this title","CodificationSection was enacted as part of the Water Resources Development Act of 2020, and not as part of the Water Resources Development Act of 1986 which comprises this chapter.","Amendments2022—Subsec. (a)(1). , added par. (1) and struck out former par. (1) which defined eligible pump station.Pub. L. 117–263, § 8152(1)Subsec. (b). , added subsec. (b) and struck out former subsec. (b). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The Secretary may carry out rehabilitation of an eligible pump station, if the Secretary determines that the rehabilitation is feasible.”Pub. L. 117–263, § 8152(2)Subsec. (g). , added subsec. (g).Pub. L. 117–263, § 8152(3)","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","“Secretary” DefinedSecretary means the Secretary of the Army, see , set out as a note under .section 2 of div. AA of Pub. L. 116–260section 2201 of this title"],"amendments":["Amendments2022—Subsec. (a)(1). , added par. (1) and struck out former par. (1) which defined eligible pump station.Pub. L. 117–263, § 8152(1)Subsec. (b). , added subsec. (b) and struck out former subsec. (b). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The Secretary may carry out rehabilitation of an eligible pump station, if the Secretary determines that the rehabilitation is feasible.”Pub. L. 117–263, § 8152(2)Subsec. (g). , added subsec. (g).Pub. L. 117–263, § 8152(3)"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Definitions","label":"a Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Eligible pump station","label":"1 Eligible pump station","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/1/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a federally authorized flood or coastal storm risk management project; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/1/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an integrated flood risk reduction system that includes a federally authorized flood or coastal storm risk management project; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the failure of which the Secretary has determined would demonstrably impact the function of the federally authorized flood or coastal storm risk management project.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Rehabilitation","label":"2 Rehabilitation","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “rehabilitation”, with respect to an eligible pump station, means to address a major deficiency of the eligible pump station caused by long-term degradation of the foundation, construction materials, or engineering systems or components of the eligible pump station.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Inclusions","label":"B Inclusions","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa%2F2%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/B/i/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/B/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa%2F2%2FB%2Fi%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"current design standards;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/B/i/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/B/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa%2F2%2FB%2Fi%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"efficiency improvements; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"III","heading":null,"label":"III","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/B/i/III","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/B/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa%2F2%2FB%2Fi%2FIII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"associated drainage; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa%2F2%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/B/ii/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/B/ii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa%2F2%2FB%2Fii%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"significantly decrease the risk of loss of life and property damage; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/B/ii/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/a/2/B/ii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fa%2F2%2FB%2Fii%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"decrease total lifecycle rehabilitation costs for the eligible pump station.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Authorization","label":"b Authorization","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the eligible pump station has a major deficiency; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the rehabilitation is feasible.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Cost sharing","label":"c Cost sharing","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provide 35 percent of the cost of rehabilitation of an eligible pump station carried out under this section; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provide all land, easements, rights-of-way, and necessary relocations associated with the rehabilitation described in subparagraph (A), at no cost to the Federal Government.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Agreement required","label":"d Agreement required","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to pay the non-Federal share of the costs of rehabilitation under subsection (c); and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to pay 100 percent of the operation and maintenance costs of the rehabilitated eligible pump station, in accordance with regulations promulgated by the Secretary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":"Treatment","label":"e Treatment","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The rehabilitation of an eligible pump station pursuant to this section shall not be considered to be a separable element of the associated flood risk management project constructed by the Corps of Engineers.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":"Authorization of appropriations","label":"f Authorization of appropriations","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"There is authorized to be appropriated to carry out this section $60,000,000, to remain available until expended.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"g","heading":"Prioritization","label":"g Prioritization","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a/g","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327a%2Fg","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To the maximum extent practicable, the Secretary shall prioritize the rehabilitation of eligible pump stations under this section that benefit economically disadvantaged communities, as defined by the Secretary under section 160 of the Water Resources Development Act of 2020 ( note), including economically disadvantaged communities located in urban and rural areas.33 U.S.C. 2201","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
